<dl id="n09070e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09070e">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09070e"> 70(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> dwarfs at French / court buglers etc</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Pendant longtemps, les nains furent tr&egrave;s &agrave; la mode &agrave; la cour de France; dans le principe, ils ne servaient pas de simple divertissement, ils remplissaient des fonctions pour lesquels ils &eacute;taient r&eacute;tribu&eacute;s. Ils sonnaient du cor sur le donjon du ch&acirc;teau o&ugrave; ils se tenaient, afin de signaler l&apos;arriv&eacute;e des dames et des cavaliers d&apos;importance. <br><font color="green">[For a long time dwarves were very fashionable at the French Court. From the outset they were not just there for amusement, but performed offices for which they were paid. They sounded the horn on the castle keep where they were stationed, in order to announce the arrival of ladies and escorts of consequence.]</font> <small> Caufeynon, <a name="CAUF" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CAUF"><cite title="source">Les Monstres Humains</cite></a> (Paris, 1900) 108</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
